cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 175 miles SW of Fort Myers, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving north-northeast in the east-central Gulf, forecast to turn NE and cross the Florida peninsula, then emerge into the western Atlantic off northeast Florida/Georgia
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: west-central Florida coast near Tampa Bay to Cedar Key

weather_observation.watch_coast: Hurricane Watch: Anna Maria Island to Yankeetown; Tropical Storm Watch: north of Suwannee River to Aucilla River, FL and portions of western Cuba
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning: Dry Tortugas and Bonita Beach to Suwannee River, FL; Storm Surge Watch: Bonita Beach to Steinhatchee River including Tampa Bay and Charlotte Harbor
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Southwest and west-central Florida coastline, across the Florida peninsula, and portions of the southeast U.S. Atlantic coast
weather_observation.wind: Periods of tropical-storm-force gusts (30–40 mph) possible Thursday night into Friday morning
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected on the Atlantic side; surge threat confined to Florida’s Gulf coast
weather_observation.rainfall: 2–4 inches of rain possible with locally higher amounts, leading to ponding of water and minor flooding
weather_observation.other_hazards: High surf, rip currents, and rough seas in and near the channel approaches beginning late Thursday
